Academyâ€™s initial journey was started with the important Mime-sketches like THAG, BECHARI PAKHI, DUSTU CHELE, and PUTUL GHAR and was widely acclaimed by the innumerable art lovers of our country. In 1993 BONUS was produced â€“ a different kind of language of mime emerged with the application of other elements of theatre. The production has been accepted as an advance experiment through that time. Another kind of experimental theatre through any kind of space has been done through some Japanese Kiogens. Kiogen is a kind of satire drama, acted in Japan. In this sphere Nirbak Abhinoy Academy produced JOYGURU and KATTABABUR KISSA. These two productions are translated in Bengali by Pabitra Sarkar. In order to remain always faithful, the troupe over the year has launched KANAN PISIR JAPAMALA, a unique production based on Hindu-Widow of 19th century Bengali Society. The play is indebted to a book of social history written by Kalyani Dutta. An extensive research work of the playwright-director SURANJANA DASGUPTA has brought forth the play. The troupe has also participated in different Theatre Festivals including Hutch Odeon Theatre Festival 2005, a prestigious Theatre Festival of recent time. The troupe has performed DULALI, an adaptation of Ibsenâ€™s The Wild Duck in Natya Swapno Kalpo, a renowned theatre festival of Kolkata on 31st December of 2006. Another production is based on corporal movement titled HEADLINES. The text is non-verbal. Itâ€™s a presentation of agony and protest against our social, political, economic, physical and mental exploitation. Next production titled BANOJOCHONA has been launched in April 2007. The drama has been written by Manoj Mitra, a renowned playwright of West Bengal. Suranjana Dasgupta is the director of this play. Another eminent work titled NIROB KATHA has been launched in the month of June 2007. It is a joint production in collaboration with another theatre group Bhraman and has been directed by a guest director K.R.Omkar, a pass-out from National School of Drama (New Delhi). The drama was produced in Bengali and has been translated by Suranjana Dasgupta. A theatre festival was held by us in Nandan Chattar, Abanindra Shabha Griho and Sisir Mancha. It was a festival of two days named Du Din Bhar Natok. 13th of October was the first day of the festival. A short play MONIKAHINI has been launched on 23rd March, 2008 at Sujata Sadan. This play has been sponsored by Sangeet Natak Academy. Itâ€™s our first programme of Children Theatre. The play has been written and directed by Suranjana Dasgupta. We also have performed Kanan Pisir Japomala in Nandipat Theatre Festival, named Narir Mancho on 8th March`10, Womenâ€™s Day. Our new production is named TIN GUCHHIR BINUNI. ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: The groupâ€™s first production, Nathabati Anaathabat, was staged in 1983. The production has received houseful shows whenever staged. Though rare, but this production is staged once every alternate years even now.This play was also performed in Hindi and has got similar accolades. Pancham Vaidic inorder to do something meaningful and creative in the domain of theatre, has set up a theatre institute, Panchamveda Charyashram, a centre to impart training in all aspects of theatre in 1984. Students here learn the language of the body, attempt at experiments with voice and speech, and try to imbibe the idioms of theatre. There are classes on the origin and history of drama as well as elementary science also.We are regularly receiving interested students and there are regular training program conducted round the year to train aspiring future theatre artistes. This training is without any cost to the students. The workshops are lead by eminent personalities from theatre world, spearheaded by Smt Saoli Mitra. The groupâ€™s second production, Kathaa Amrita Saman, was produced in January 1990. This play is also adored by Indian intelligentsia and has done regular houseful shows. Even now, on popular demand, we perform this play once every alternate year. We have set up Tripti Mitra Sangrahasala, an archive in the memory of Late Smt Tripti Mitra, doyen of Indian theatre, in 1993. The archive has a collection of her awards, costumes, personal belongings and furniture. Audio cassettes of her interviews, plays and recitations are played on request. Members of Pancham Vaidic are dedicated in maintaining this archive. In 1994, we performed Bitata Bitangsha, followed by plays like Agnimantha, Sujan Bratir Simanta, Antargata Agun and audio plays like Hafiz Miyar Nao. These plays, due to various reasons, are not performed anymore. Our current production are Rajnaitik Hatya (adaptation from Sratreâ€™s Les Main Sales) directed by Saoli Mitra Chandali, by Gurudev Rabindranath Tagore, acted by Saoli Mitra & Arpita Ghosh in leading roles. Poshu Khamar (adaptation of George Orwellâ€™s Animal Farm) acted by Debatosh Ghosh, Saoli Mitra and 35 other actors on stage. Tokolosh, Narakiya, Ganesh A-parajita â€“ based on 3 short stories of Gurudev Rabindranath Tagore on the theme of women power. Ghare Baire, famous political novel written by Rabindranath Tagore to commemorate his 150th birth anniversary acted by Santilal Mukherjee, Debdoot Ghosh and acted/directed by Arpita Ghosh Working on Arthur Koestlarâ€™s Darkness at Noon, planned to staged in August this year. Our current productions are regularly staged in leading auditoriums of Kolkata like Academy of Fine Arts, Rabindra Sadan, Madhusudan Manch, Tapan Theatre, Sujata Sadan, Kalamandir etc. Regularly on an average we are doing 2-3 shows of the above productions every month. Apart from shows in Kolkata, we have invitational performances in other districts of West Bengal and other parts of India such as Bangalore, Ahmedabad, Mumbai, Delhi, Bhopal etc. We regularly take part in Bharat Rang Mahotsava organized by National School of Drama in New Delhi and have got extreme popularity in their festivals. In addition to the above, every year we have our in-house programs to commemorate the birth and death anniversaries of our founder and doyen of Indian thetare Sri Shambhu Mitra & Smt Tripti Mitra. The program is attended by close well wishers of the Group.
